{
  "_doc": "Modern Horizons 3 (MH3) Play + Collector recipes. Source: Wizards 'Collecting Modern Horizons 3' (https://magic.wizards.com/en/news/feature/collecting-modern-horizons-3). MH3 had NO standard Draft Booster \u2014 Play Boosters are the draftable product \u2014 so only play + collector are defined and authoritative is true (draft is hidden). The 'New-to-Modern' bonus-sheet slot pulls cards from the MH3 Commander set; we approximate it with the MH3 Commander code M3C. Retro frame (classic 1997-style framing, 58 MH3 cards) now uses the dedicated retro_frame filter instead of a showcase stand-in, across the Play rare/mythic + New-to-Modern slots and the Collector retro-frame / rare-mythic / Booster Fun slots. Full-art Eldrazi lands and full-art Snow-Covered Wastes now use the full_art filter instead of basic_land. Remaining Booster Fun treatments (frame break, profile) have no dedicated filter and stay folded into borderless, noted inline. Textured-foil Special Guests / ripple-foil chases stay on special_guest / serialized as before. Special Guests reference the SPG promo set. Jumpstart, Commander decks, Prerelease, and Bundles are intentionally omitted. [Chase fix: added textured-foil outcomes so MH3 textured foils are reachable.]",
